<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - 3300 Model - CHASSIS FEATURES - PYROMETER/AMMETER MODULE (PAM) -
        DIAGNOSTICS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DIAGNOSTICS</title>
        <table id="t08298156" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Pyrometer/Ammeter Module (PAM) Preliminary Check</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.52in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.51in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.78in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.47in"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES - IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO - OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Attempt to operate the Pyrometer/Ammeter Module (PAM).</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>(PAM) operate.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>(PAM) is working.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>With (PAM) switch on, check switch lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Visually check status of switch lamp.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Switch lamp stays on.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Problem is in air system. Check air lines.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                            <para>Determine if any other features are malfunctioning that may have common circuits
                                (Example: Missing ground common to several features).
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                            <para>Visually check for other malfunc- tioning features.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                            <para>No other features are malfunc- tioning.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                            <para>Identify and repair condition causing several features to be inoperative.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>
                                <hotlnk xrefid="x08298155">Check for ESC diagnostic trouble codes.</hotlnk>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Read display on odometer.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Diagnostic trouble codes for ABS are active.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0">
                            <para>Consider replacing the ESC.
                                <hotlnk document="s08298_X08298212.xml" xrefid="x08298212">Refer to ESC Replacement in
                                    this manual.
                                </hotlnk>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="SPAN1" rotate="0">
                            <para>Cross reference the DTC to the applicable section from the
                                <hotlnk document="s08298_FC.xml" xrefid="x08298211">DTC table</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>Problems in PAM could be the result of open or shorted circuits, a failure in the ESC or a problem with
            the PAM.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f082981035">Pyrometer/Ammeter Module Circuits</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f082981035" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg08/g08298548.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="432px"/>
            <caption>Pyrometer/Ammeter Module Circuits - Always Refer to Circuit Diagram Book for Latest Circuit
                Information
            </caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>(1011) FUSE BLOCK
                    <callout2>LOCATED LEFT SIDE VEHICLE AT FLASHER PLATE</callout2>
                </callout1>
                <callout1>(4014) DASH/ENGINE PASS THRU
                    <callout2>LOCATED AT INSIDE LEFT SIDE DASH PANEL</callout2>
                </callout1>
                <callout1>(4087) PYROMETER/AMMETER MODULE
                    <callout2>LOCATED OUTSIDE RIGHT SIDE DASH PANEL</callout2>
                </callout1>
                <callout1>(6332) (6333) AMMETER SENSE
                    <callout2>LOCATED AT STARTER</callout2>
                </callout1>
                <callout1>(6350) GROUND SPLICE PACK
                    <callout2>LOCATED AT ENGINE COMPARTMENT NEAR STARTER</callout2>
                </callout1>
                <callout1>(9262) BATTERY AMMETER SENSE
                    <callout2>LOCATED AT AMMETER SENSE CABLE</callout2>
                </callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <table id="t08298157" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Pyrometer/Ammeter Module Diagnostic Trouble Codes</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.71in"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="3.91in"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>639 14 82 254</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>Pyrometer Ammeter not communicating with ESC.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <table id="t08259a1" tblwidth="full-page" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Pyrometer/Ammeter Module Tests</title>
            <tgroup cols="6">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="0.77in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.89in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.87in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" colwidth="1.51in"/>
                <spanspec namest="3" nameend="6" spanname="SPAN2"/>
                <spanspec namest="4" nameend="6" spanname="S4T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="6" spanname="S1T6"/>
                <spanspec namest="2" nameend="3" spanname="S2T3"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="6" spanname="S1T6" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="BOLD">Pyrometer/Ammeter Module Voltage Checks</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>Check with ignition on and PAM connector (4087) disconnected.</para>
                            <note>
                                <para>Always check connectors for damage and pushed-out terminals.</para>
                            </note>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>Test Points</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>Spec.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6" align="center">
                            <para>Comments</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(4087) cavity 6 to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open fuse F4 in fuse block (1011). Also check for
                                open or shorts in circuit K26D, or A26.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(4087) cavity 6 to cavity 12.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open in circuit J11-GM to ground splice connection
                                (6350).
                            </para>
                            <para>If circuits are good and voltage still missing, check connection from ground splice
                                (6350) to ground.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(4087) cavity 6 to cavity 10.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open in circuit K26B, or N26B.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>(4087) cavity 6 to cavity 11.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="2" spanname="S2T3">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colspan="3" spanname="S4T6">
                            <para>If voltage is missing, check for open in circuits J26A or K26A.</para>
                            <para>If all voltages are present, circuits to PAM are good. Replace PAM.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
